class Solution {
    public int minAddToMakeValid(String s) {
        int count = 0;
        int balance = 0;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (c == '(') {
                balance++;
            } else {
                balance--;
                if (balance < 0) {
                    count++;
                    balance = 0;
                }
            }
        }
        return count + balance;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(N)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the string once, maintaining a balance counter. When the balance becomes negative, it increments the count and resets the balance. At the end, it returns the count plus the remaining balance, effectively counting the minimum number of moves required to make the string valid.
